yay -S stgit
'stg refresh --index' will note the chnages made in the index.
'stg new <name>' Will name chnages observed with the recent index refresh.
'stg applied' list all the patches -changes- appllied.
'stg pop patch1' will remove patch1 from recent index.
'stg push patch1' will add patch1 to recnt index.

Example:
#made some chnages in HEAD.
$ stg new patch1
$ git add -i
$ stg refresh --index
$ stg new patch2
$ git add -i
$ stg refresh --index

$ stg applied
patch1
patch2
<... do tests using both patches ...>
$ stg pop patch1
<... do tests using only patch2 ...>
$ stg pop patch2
$ stg push patch1
<... do tests using only patch1 ...>
$ stg push -a
$ stg commit -a  # commit all the patches
